					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on Numbers.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he">Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="96v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Be-midbar </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש במדבר </title>
							<note>
								<p>Fragment of an Arabic commentary on Numbers 19:4-23:16. </p>
								<p>Includes a translation of the Hebrew text, being probably part of the shorter recension of Abu al-Faraj Furḳan's Commentary on the Pentateuch. </p>
								<p>The longer recension of the commentary is quoted on chapters 19:15, 16, 22 and 21:17, folios 34v, 37v, 42v, 62v.</p>
								<p>Quotes several Karaite authorities.</p>
								<p>The Arabic translation is arranged in the following sections: chapters 20:1-13, 14-21, 20:22-21:3, 21:4-20, 21:21-22:1, 22:2-23:12.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269" xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Abu al-Faraj Furḳan, active 11th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269" xml:lang="he">ישועה בן יהודה  </persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>The translation of chapters 21:18-22, folios 57r &amp; 63v, agrees with Or 2491 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">93</ref>), folio 32r.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; a cursive Naskhi hand, of probably 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>96 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>135/160</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>135</height>
										<width>95/110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>96 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 11 quires of 10 leaves each, imperfect at the beginning and at the end. </p>
									<p>Signatures in Arabic words on the left-hand upper corner of the first page of a quire. </p>
									<p>The original numbering of quires 4-10 was 3-9. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Lacuna after folio 95. </p>
									<p>Stained. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="14 22" writtenLines="14 22">
									<p>14 to 15 lines a page on folios 1-18 and 89-90, and 20 to 22 on folios 19-88. </p>
									<p>Biblical text in Hebrew characters is embodied. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>A cursive Naskhi hand, of probably 13th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="18v"/>and <locus from="89r" to="96v"/>have been supplied by a different hand of about the same date.</p>
							</handNote>
